This way.

247
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:49,779
Baby, Xiao Ran.

248
00:17:53,900 --> 00:17:56,440
How come you came back together?

249
00:17:58,019 --> 00:18:00,699
Mom, Uncle Ding.

250
00:18:00,699 --> 00:18:02,079
Dad.

251
00:18:02,079 --> 00:18:04,280
- I've had dinner. I'm going home first.
- I'm going shopping.

252
00:18:04,280 --> 00:18:07,260
Xile, Ding Ran, wait a minute.

253
00:18:07,260 --> 00:18:09,280
You came back just in time.

254
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:13,940
About our marriage, Senyun and I hope that you can—

255
00:18:13,940 --> 00:18:17,179
Live peacefully together, right? We will. Please continue.

256
00:18:17,179 --> 00:18:22,219
Baobei and I mean to have you be our bridesmaid and groomsman.

257
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:27,780
Mom, what's this?

258
00:18:27,780 --> 00:18:33,059
Your mother and I decided to get married after much consideration.

259
00:18:33,059 --> 00:18:35,279
Now that you've both grown up,

260
00:18:35,279 --> 00:18:39,839
we want to hear your thoughts on some wedding details.

261
00:18:43,179 --> 00:18:46,060
Spring Festival… Must be spent at the bride's hometown.

262
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:47,939
I think that's fine.

263
00:18:47,939 --> 00:18:51,880
We could change a place every year. Next year, we can go to your hometown.

264
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:57,080
- The wedding should also be held in the bride's hometown.
- If you're not short of money, hold one in both.

265
00:18:57,900 --> 00:19:00,360
If there are children after the marriage…

266
00:19:00,360 --> 00:19:02,979
Can my dad still have children?

267
00:19:02,979 --> 00:19:05,879
You brat, what are you talking about?

268
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:09,600
When you're married, children come automatically. You should always plan ahead.

269
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,860
- Even the second child is considered.
- What's wrong with the second child?

270
00:19:11,860 --> 00:19:14,780
- Don't you know now—
- Wait a minute.

271
00:19:14,780 --> 00:19:17,719
Why does it feel like you two are getting married?

272
00:19:17,719 --> 00:19:19,859
Who wants to marry him?

273
00:19:19,859 --> 00:19:22,299
- In high school, someone wasn't—
- Ding Ran!

274
00:19:22,299 --> 00:19:24,800
I warn you. Don't belittle me.

275
00:19:24,800 --> 00:19:29,299
Baby, you're a girl. Don't be so rude to your brother.

276
00:19:29,299 --> 00:19:33,540
- I—
- Ding Ran, did you bully your sister all the time in high school?

277
00:19:35,740 --> 00:19:39,499
Now that you two are determined to get married, I have two conditions.

278
00:19:39,499 --> 00:19:40,620
Go ahead.

279
00:19:40,620 --> 00:19:43,940
First, I will absolutely not call her sister anymore.

280
00:19:43,940 --> 00:19:46,399
As if anyone wants to hear you call sister.

281
00:19:46,399 --> 00:19:52,399
Second, if she's the bridesmaid, I absolutely won't be the groomsman.

282
00:19:55,499 --> 00:19:59,639
Don't worry, if you're the groomsman, I definitely won't be the bridesmaid.

283
00:20:04,840 --> 00:20:08,459
Senyun, their relationship is so bad.

284
00:20:08,459 --> 00:20:11,140
Can we still get married?

285
00:20:13,479 --> 00:20:18,440
Seems like we need to find a way to improve their relationship.

286
00:20:21,039 --> 00:20:26,500
Jiang Xile, you can consider quitting your job and focus on running this store with me.

287
00:20:28,159 --> 00:20:30,159
You don't need a relationship that ties you down.

288
00:20:30,159 --> 00:20:34,219
But I need a stable job to secure my mom's later years.

289
00:20:34,219 --> 00:20:36,219
- Let me do it, Xiao Ke.
- Baby.

290
00:20:36,219 --> 00:20:40,120
In this world, nothing is stable.

291
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:44,400
Lu Liuliu, are you still upset about your ex-boyfriend?

292
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:46,160
He's nothing.

293
00:20:46,160 --> 00:20:50,039
You don't know how happy and carefree I am now.

294
00:20:50,039 --> 00:20:51,979
I hope it's true.

295
00:20:51,979 --> 00:20:55,579
You and your motorcycle boy have been WeChat contacts for nearly 72 hours.

296
00:20:55,579 --> 00:20:58,559
If he still doesn't contact you, what will you do?

297
00:20:58,559 --> 00:20:59,720
Then unfriend him.

298
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:03,920
A woman should never take the initiative, no matter how much she likes a man.

299
00:21:03,920 --> 00:21:07,139
I never break my 72-hour rule.

300
00:21:12,620 --> 00:21:14,580
He contacted you?

301
00:21:19,480 --> 00:21:21,879
Old rules.

302
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:27,780
Impossible. You said he was very innocent.

303
00:21:27,780 --> 00:21:31,160
You can't pick this flower.

304
00:21:33,540 --> 00:21:37,660
Qi Fei, are you at the store entrance now? I'm in the store now.

305
00:21:37,660 --> 00:21:38,980
Please come in.

306
00:21:38,980 --> 00:21:40,540
The motorcycle boy?

307
00:21:40,540 --> 00:21:42,360
Miss Lu.

308
00:21:43,839 --> 00:21:47,459
- So handsome.
- I've lost myself.

309
00:21:49,076 --> 00:21:51,120
- Qi Fei.
- I'm sorry.

310
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,160
I came suddenly without notice.

311
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:55,319
It's okay. It's okay.

312
00:21:56,299 --> 00:21:58,740
This is my good friend, Xile.

313
00:21:58,740 --> 00:22:01,160
- Hello.
- Hello.

314
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:03,859
You are…

315
00:22:05,939 --> 00:22:08,360
Excuse me, I need to take a call.

316
00:22:09,712 --> 00:22:11,640
- By the way,
- Hello, Ping'an.

317
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:15,580
- Xile, are you home?
- Your coat is still in my house. I have to give it back to you next time.
- I am not home.

318
00:22:15,580 --> 00:22:18,599
- That's okay. It's only a coat. I have many.
- When are you free?
- Not sure yet.

319
00:22:18,599 --> 00:22:22,920
If you're free, let's go fishing in the afternoon. We can take the fish to your house for dinner.

320
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:25,500
- Okay, see you later.
- Okay, I'll let you go.

321
00:22:25,500 --> 00:22:27,340
Lu Liuliu.

322
00:22:29,079 --> 00:22:31,980
- Where are they?
- They're gone.

323
00:22:31,980 --> 00:22:33,539
Gone?

324
00:22:33,539 --> 00:22:35,204
Gone.

325
00:22:39,259 --> 00:22:43,684
Xiao Ting, has Jiang Xile's medical report come out yet?

326
00:22:43,684 --> 00:22:47,039
Jiang Xile? Let me check.

327
00:22:49,580 --> 00:22:51,339
It will be out next Monday.

328
00:22:51,339 --> 00:22:55,280
Okay. When it comes out, please let me know as soon as possible.

329
00:22:55,280 --> 00:22:57,480
- Okay.
- Thank you.

330
00:23:05,039 --> 00:23:06,999
Really?

331
00:23:06,999 --> 00:23:08,319
So fun.

332
00:23:08,319 --> 00:23:09,920
Xile never mentioned it.

333
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:11,940
Yeah, what happened after that?

334
00:23:11,940 --> 00:23:15,000
- Afterwards…
- Ding Ran is back. Come over.

335
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:18,839
Meet him. This is Xile's boyfriend.

336
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:24,920
Not yet.

337
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:27,820
Right, not yet.

338
00:23:30,059 --> 00:23:32,219
Hello, I'm Xile's friend.

339
00:23:32,219 --> 00:23:36,760
My name is Zhang Ping'an. We met at the entrance of the residential area a few nights ago.

340
00:23:43,219 --> 00:23:45,760
- Have more.
- Thank you, Auntie.

341
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:47,600
Xiao Zhang.

342
00:23:48,259 --> 00:23:51,200
What do you think of Xile?

343
00:23:52,059 --> 00:23:55,560
Mom, why ask such a question?

344
00:23:56,399 --> 00:23:59,779
Auntie, Xile is really interesting.

345
00:23:59,779 --> 00:24:01,380
Interesting?

346
00:24:01,380 --> 00:24:03,060
What do you mean?

347
00:24:03,060 --> 00:24:05,800
I just told him a few cold jokes.

348
00:24:05,800 --> 00:24:09,580
Interesting means apart from being funny, nothing else is interesting.

349
00:24:11,199 --> 00:24:12,940
Xile is interesting.

350
00:24:12,940 --> 00:24:16,940
Every moment I'm with her, I'm very happy.

351
00:24:21,480 --> 00:24:26,719
Xiao Zhang, you mentioned earlier you were researching robots?

352
00:24:26,719 --> 00:24:30,800
Uncle, I'm researching service robots for special environments,

353
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:34,079
such as disaster relief, map surveys, etc.

354
00:24:38,039 --> 00:24:39,688
- Xiao Zhang.
- Yes.

355
00:24:41,019 --> 00:24:42,659
Have more.

356
00:24:44,620 --> 00:24:46,860
Xiao Zhang, don't be so formal.

357
00:24:46,860 --> 00:24:50,639
Our family is very casual. Eat and chat, eat and chat.

358
00:24:52,099 --> 00:24:54,299
What you said earlier seems really impressive.

359
00:24:54,299 --> 00:24:56,860
Yeah, it is impressive.

360
00:24:56,860 --> 00:24:59,760
Robot researches robot.

361
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:01,979
Ding Ran, sit straight.

362
00:25:03,119 --> 00:25:06,620
Mom, why does Uncle Ding always asks Ding Ran to sit straight?

363
00:25:06,620 --> 00:25:09,660
Uncle Ding used to be an instructor.

364
00:25:09,660 --> 00:25:12,400
A dog training instructor.

365
00:25:18,320 --> 00:25:21,280
Look at Xiao Zhang. Good job, good character.

366
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:25,580
He can even fish. The fish you're eating was caught by him this afternoon.

367
00:25:25,580 --> 00:25:28,019
What can you do as an adult?

368
00:25:35,199 --> 00:25:38,599
Uncle Ding, he can bully me.

369
00:25:38,599 --> 00:25:42,319
Jiang Xile, don't push your luck.

370
00:25:42,319 --> 00:25:44,620
Be nicer to your sister.

371
00:25:48,460 --> 00:25:50,440
- Xiao Zhang.
- Yes.

372
00:25:51,119 --> 00:25:54,380
The wedding of your Aunt Xiao and I is missing a groomsman.

373
00:25:54,380 --> 00:25:58,559
Would you like to come with Xile as our groomsman and bridesmaid?

374
00:26:00,680 --> 00:26:01,940
Yeah.

375
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:05,320
Your names together just happen to form "peace and joy."

376
00:26:05,320 --> 00:26:06,499
How festive!

377
00:26:06,499 --> 00:26:08,540
That's true.

378
00:26:08,540 --> 00:26:09,940
Okay.

379
00:26:09,940 --> 00:26:11,299
Dad, you forgot it.

380
00:26:11,299 --> 00:26:15,480
The master told you at the beginning of the year that you and people with the surname Zhang had a clash.

381
00:26:18,419 --> 00:26:21,099
This kid loves to joke.

382
00:26:22,479 --> 00:26:27,500
Ding Ran, your nonsense today is a bit too much.

383
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,899
Eat, eat.

384
00:26:40,900 --> 00:26:43,320
I'm home.

385
00:26:43,900 --> 00:26:46,700
Thank you for taking me home.

386
00:26:48,560 --> 00:26:52,160
Shall we go for a cup of tea?

387
00:26:53,500 --> 00:26:57,720
It's so late and we'll drink tea?

388
00:27:05,639 --> 00:27:08,320
♫ I'm a mess ♫

389
00:27:08,320 --> 00:27:10,864
♫ Love is poison ♫

390
00:27:10,864 --> 00:27:12,632
♫ What should I do? ♫

391
00:27:12,632 --> 00:27:16,848
♫ Seeing you makes my heart beat fast ♫

392
00:27:16,848 --> 00:27:18,770
Aren't we going to have some tea?

393
00:27:18,770 --> 00:27:21,770
♫ I want to hug you ♫

394
00:27:21,770 --> 00:27:24,600
Do you really want tea?

395
00:27:24,600 --> 00:27:26,240
No.

396
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,600
♫ Sipping on ice-cold Coke, I'm feeling exceptionally chill ♫

397
00:27:28,600 --> 00:27:31,487
♫ Humming your song under my breath ♫

398
00:27:31,487 --> 00:27:32,948
♫ I look like a hooligan ♫

399
00:27:32,948 --> 00:27:34,524
♫ But I'm warm and want to... ♫

400
00:27:34,524 --> 00:27:36,020
♫ Move into your heart immediately ♫

401
00:27:36,020 --> 00:27:39,036
♫ It's like I've caught a cold ♫

402
00:27:39,036 --> 00:27:41,697
♫ I'm seriously ill since I met you ♫

403
00:27:41,697 --> 00:27:44,163
♫ I can't sleep, I'm a little upset ♫

404
00:27:44,163 --> 00:27:46,897
♫ You're the nicotine I can't quit ♫

405
00:27:46,897 --> 00:27:52,007
♫ Time is ticking ♫

406
00:27:52,007 --> 00:27:57,360
♫ The remnants of the night make me melancholy ♫

407
00:28:00,238 --> 00:28:03,996
[One Month Ago]

408
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:10,720
Jiang Xile, long time no see.

409
00:28:10,720 --> 00:28:13,180
Jiang Xile, long time no see.

410
00:28:13,180 --> 00:28:15,259
Jiang Xile,

411
00:28:15,259 --> 00:28:17,099
long time no see.

412
00:28:17,740 --> 00:28:21,240
Jiang Xile, long time no see.

413
00:28:21,240 --> 00:28:22,979
Jiang Xile...

414
00:28:23,560 --> 00:28:25,060
I…

415
00:28:25,695 --> 00:28:28,780
♫ How do we reconcile? ♫

416
00:28:28,780 --> 00:28:31,040
What should I say?

417
00:28:33,943 --> 00:28:39,160
♫ There are always some answers that will never be revealed ♫

418
00:28:41,900 --> 00:28:45,780
Dad, I heard the next-door neighbors were moving out in a few days.

419
00:28:45,780 --> 00:28:47,540
What's up?

420
00:28:47,540 --> 00:28:49,188
Nothing.

421
00:28:49,979 --> 00:28:52,920
Dad, are our next-door neighbors moving today?

422
00:28:52,920 --> 00:28:56,039
Yes, what's up?

423
00:28:56,039 --> 00:28:57,380
Nothing.

424
00:28:57,380 --> 00:28:59,140
They're disturbing me.

425
00:29:01,860 --> 00:29:05,320
Dad, is the next-door house still vacant?

426
00:29:05,320 --> 00:29:08,380
Yes, it's vacant. What's up?

427
00:29:08,380 --> 00:29:10,179
Nothing.

428
00:29:10,179 --> 00:29:11,816
Ding Ran,

429
00:29:13,039 --> 00:29:16,460
I want Aunt Xiao and Xile to move next door,

430
00:29:16,460 --> 00:29:19,720
so our two families can develop a relationship in advance. What do you think?

431
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:21,580
Whatever you want.

432
00:29:22,640 --> 00:29:25,139
Well, I think you are a member of this family.

433
00:29:25,139 --> 00:29:27,759
I should discuss everything with you.

434
00:29:28,460 --> 00:29:31,260
You brat, what's with the attitude?

435
00:29:33,151 --> 00:29:35,900
♫ It dawned on me overnight that after all the twists and turns, I still love you deeply ♫

436
00:29:35,900 --> 00:29:39,819
Jiang Xile, long time no see.

437
00:29:39,819 --> 00:29:42,661
♫ Back then, I was oblivious, pushing you away and regrets unravel as we reunite ♫

438
00:29:42,661 --> 00:29:46,329
♫ Back then, I was oblivious, pushing you away and regrets unravel as we reunite ♫

439
00:29:46,329 --> 00:29:49,208
♫ I want to wait until we both have white hair ♫

440
00:29:49,208 --> 00:29:53,596
♫ Together we can make up for the love we missed ♫

441
00:29:53,596 --> 00:29:59,452
♫ I really want to hold you in my arms again ♫

442
00:29:59,452 --> 00:30:03,842
♫ I won't let go again ♫

443
00:30:14,836 --> 00:30:20,660
♫ I'm blessed to encounter a meaningful bond ♫

444
00:30:21,392 --> 00:30:25,543
♫ Saying, "I like you," comes too late ♫

445
00:30:25,543 --> 00:30:28,982
♫ Thinking back to when we first met ♫

446
00:30:28,982 --> 00:30:33,834
♫ I had sweaty palms and my senses awestruck ♫

447
00:30:33,834 --> 00:30:40,223
♫ Ten years of missed opportunity, now reunited with regret ♫
